cs.LO, cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.FL, cs.AI

The paper deals with language-theoretic results and games with reachability objectives, which are typically studied in the areas of logic and automata theory (cs.LO) and game theory (cs.GT). The use of weighted automata on infinite words also suggests a connection to formal language theory (cs.FL) and algorithms for manipulating infinite data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the mention of undecidability hints at a potential connection to computational complexity theory and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
